Quick overview
**************

For a quick tutorial see @{"Tutorial.guide" link "Tutorial.guide/Main"}.

@{b}MPMorph@{ub} is a set of morphing programs. It consists of two programs:

     @{b}MPMorph@{ub}   Edit the Morph parameters
     @{b}MPRender@{ub}  Generate the morphed images

See @{"MPRender.guide" link "MPRender.guide/main"} for information on
the render program.


@EndNode

@Node "Installation" "MPMorph.guide/Installation"
@Next "Requirements"
@Prev "Overview"
@Toc "Main"

Installation instructions
*************************

If you wish to use @{b}Installer@{ub} then @{b}MPMorph@{ub} can be installed using the
supplied script. If not then you are on your own!


@EndNode

@Node "Requirements" "MPMorph.guide/Requirements"
@Next "Par"
@Prev "Installation"
@Toc "Main"

Software and Hardware required
******************************

OS3.0+ is required to run MPMorph.

The following are used if present:

     reqtools.library         38 reqtools is ©1991/1992 Nico François
                                 This is required for Animated Warps/Morphs
     egs.library              0  EGS is © Copyright 1990/93 VIONA Development.
     egsintui.library         0
     egsgfx.library           0
     egsrequest.library       0


@EndNode

@Node "Par" "MPMorph.guide/Par"
@Next "Info"
@Prev "Requirements"
@Toc "Main"

Tool types and Shell parameters
*******************************

Both @{b}MPMorph@{ub} and @{b}MPRender@{ub} can be run from the Shell or the Workbench.
Most parameters can be edited using the @{"Settings" Link "men-Settings"} menu.

Parameters can be supplied, normally either on the @{b}Shell@{ub} command line,
as Icon @{b}Tool Types@{ub} on the @{b}Project@{ub}, @{b}MPMorph@{ub} or @{b}MPRender@{ub} Icon, or in a
@{b}settings file@{ub}.

The format of settings files is a text file with lines in the format:

     Settingstype=settingsvalue

Blank lines or lines starting with a ; (semi-colon) are treated as
comments. Any settings supplied on the @{b}Shell@{ub} command line or as an Icon
@{b}Tool Type@{ub} override values specified in this file. Parameters on the
@{b}Project@{ub} Icon override parameters on the @{b}Tool@{ub} Icon.

@{b}Note:@{ub} All the @{b}Project@{ub} Icon tool types are used if the project is run
with a @{b}default@{ub} tool or by @{b}double clicking@{ub} a tool, some are not used if
the project is selected using a @{b}file requester@{ub}, if the Tool was run
from the @{b}Shell@{ub} then file requester selected project tool types are
ignored. Also some @{b}settings@{ub} can not be changed on @{b}open@{ub} projects,

The Settings file name used is first file found from:

     1) The name supplied in the @{b}SETTINGS=@{ub} parameter on the project.
     2) The name supplied in the @{b}SETTINGS=@{ub} parameter on the tool.
     3) @{b}MPMorph.prefs@{ub}
        in the @{b}project@{ub} directory for the @{b}workbench@{ub},
        the @{b}current@{ub} directory from the @{b}Shell@{ub}.
     4) @{b}MPMorph.prefs@{ub}
        in the directory @{b}MPMorph@{ub} was loaded from.
     5) @{b}ENV:MPMorph/MPMorph.prefs@{ub}

Unless @{"KEEPSETTINGS" Link "P-KEEPSETTINGS"} is set to @{b}NO@{ub} current settings are saved in
@{b}ENV:MPMorph/MPMorph.prefs@{ub} when @{b}MPMorph@{ub} is quit. Settings can be saved
and loaded from the @{"Settings" Link "men-Settings"} menu.

The following parameters can be supplied:


 @{" CREATEICONS   " Link "P-CREATEICONS"}                Create project Icons
 @{" CREATEICONSP  " Link "P-CREATEICONSP"}                Create prefs Icons
 @{" PUBSCREEN     " Link "P-PUBSCREEN"}                Public screen to use
 @{" PORTNAME      " Link "P-PORTNAME"}                ARexx Port Name
 @{" CUSTOMMODE    " Link "P-CUSTOMMODE"}                Custom screen mode
 @{" CUSTOMDEPTH   " Link "P-CUSTOMDEPTH"}                Custom screen depth
 @{" EGS           " Link "P-EGS"}                Use EGS for image windows
 @{" REQTOOLS      " Link "P-REQTOOLS"}                Use ReqTools.library
 @{" FILES         " Link "P-FILES"}                Specify file to open
 @{" HELP          " Link "P-HELP"}                Display continuous help
 @{" KEEPSETTINGS  " Link "P-KEEPSETTINGS"}                Save settings on Quit
 @{" SETTINGS      " Link "P-SETTINGS"}                Settings file name
 @{" ZOOM          " Link "P-ZOOM"}                Zoom image 2 times
 @{" PREVIEW       " Link "P-PREVIEW"}                ARexx script to preview image
 @{" USER2         " Link "P-USER2"}                Macro 2
 @{" USER3         " Link "P-USER3"}                Macro 3
 @{" USER4         " Link "P-USER4"}                Macro 4
 @{" USER5         " Link "P-USER5"}                Macro 5
 @{" USER6         " Link "P-USER6"}                Macro 6
 @{" USER7         " Link "P-USER7"}                Macro 7
 @{" USER8         " Link "P-USER8"}                Macro 8
 @{" USER9         " Link "P-USER9"}                Macro 9
 @{" RECENT1       " Link "P-RECENT1"}                Recent Open File 1
 @{" RECENT2       " Link "P-RECENT2"}                Recent Open File 2
 @{" RECENT3       " Link "P-RECENT3"}                Recent Open File 3
 @{" RECENT4       " Link "P-RECENT4"}                Recent Open File 4
 @{" RECENT5       " Link "P-RECENT5"}                Recent Open File 5


@EndNode

@Node "P-CREATEICONS" "MPMorph.guide/P-CREATEICONS"
@Next "P-CREATEICONSP"
@Toc "Par"

CREATEICONS=YES/NO
==================

Sets the default value of the @{b}Create Icons?@{ub} settings menu item -
defaults to @{b}YES@{ub}.

This item toggles if Icons are to be saved with @{"parameter files" Link "File_Format"}. If it
is selected then an Icon will be saved. The icon will come from
@{b}ENV:MPMorph/def_points@{ub} if this exists, secondly from
@{b}ENV:SYS/def_points@{ub}, otherwise the @{b}default project Icon@{ub} is used.

This parameter is not changed by Requester loaded projects.


@EndNode

@Node "P-CREATEICONSP" "MPMorph.guide/P-CREATEICONSP"
@Next "P-PUBSCREEN"
@Prev "P-CREATEICONS"
@Toc "Par"

CREATEICONSP=YES/NO
===================

Sets the default value of the @{b}Create Prefs Icons?@{ub} settings menu item -
defaults to @{b}YES@{ub}.

This item toggles if Icons are to be saved with @{"Settings" Link "Par"} files. If it is
selected then an Icon will be saved. The icon will come from
@{b}ENV:MPMorph/def_prefs@{ub} if this exists, secondly from @{b}ENV:SYS/def_prefs@{ub},
otherwise the @{b}default project Icon@{ub} is used.


@EndNode

@Node "P-PUBSCREEN" "MPMorph.guide/P-PUBSCREEN"
@Next "P-PORTNAME"
@Prev "P-CREATEICONSP"
@Toc "Par"

PUBSCREEN=pubscreenname
=======================

This gives the name of the Public Screen on which to open all @{b}MPMorph@{ub}
windows - default is the default public screen.

This parameter is not changed by Requester loaded projects.

It can be changed using the menu item, a requester is displayed
allowing the input of the screen name, but any change is ignored until
@{b}MPMorph@{ub} is reloaded.

If @{"CUSTOMMODE" Link "P-CUSTOMMODE"} is supplied as well then a public screen of this name is
opened.


@EndNode

@Node "P-PORTNAME" "MPMorph.guide/P-PORTNAME"
@Next "P-CUSTOMMODE"
@Prev "P-PUBSCREEN"
@Toc "Par"

PORTNAME=name
=============

This gives the name of the ARexx port to open.

The default is MPMORPH.

See @{"MPMorph-rexx" link "MPMorph-rexx/main"}.


@EndNode

@Node "P-CUSTOMMODE" "MPMorph.guide/P-CUSTOMMODE"
@Next "P-CUSTOMDEPTH"
@Prev "P-PORTNAME"
@Toc "Par"

CUSTOMMODE=screen_mode
======================

This gives the mode of the custom screen to open.

The mode is as show in the Screen Mode requester - case is ignored
(e.g. "PAL:Low Res"). This parameter is not changed by Requester loaded
projects.

The name of the screen must be given by the @{"PUBSCREEN" Link "P-PUBSCREEN"} parameter. The
depth is given by the @{"CUSTOMDEPTH" Link "P-CUSTOMDEPTH"} parameter. The screen will mostly
clone the Workbench, but other colours will be set up as a grey scale.

It can be changed using the menu item, a requester is displayed
allowing the input of the screen mode, but any change is ignored until
@{b}MPMorph@{ub} is reloaded.

The default value is nothing which means do not open a custom screen.


@EndNode

@Node "P-CUSTOMDEPTH" "MPMorph.guide/P-CUSTOMDEPTH"
@Next "P-EGS"
@Prev "P-CUSTOMMODE"
@Toc "Par"

CUSTOMDEPTH=4
=============

This gives the depth of the custom screen to open if @{"CUSTOMMODE" Link "P-CUSTOMMODE"} is
specified.

It can be changed using the menu item, a requester is displayed
allowing the input of the screen mode, but any change is ignored until
@{b}MPMorph@{ub} is reloaded.

The default value is 4.


@EndNode

@Node "P-EGS" "MPMorph.guide/P-EGS"
@Next "P-REQTOOLS"
@Prev "P-CUSTOMDEPTH"
@Toc "Par"

EGS=YES/NO
==========

This controls the use of @{b}EGS@{ub} when displaying the @{"edit" Link "Edit"} windows. See
@{"requirements" Link "Requirements"} for library requirements. If set to yes then the @{"edit" Link "Edit"}
windows and relevent @{"error" Link "Req-Error"} requesters are displayed on the default @{b}EGS@{ub}
screen.

@{"ZOOM" Link "P-ZOOM"} is always set to @{b}OFF@{ub} when using @{b}EGS@{ub}.

This parameter is not available as a menu option, is not saved in
settings files and can not be specified on a project Icon.

Default values is @{b}NO@{ub}.


@EndNode

@Node "P-REQTOOLS" "MPMorph.guide/P-REQTOOLS"
@Next "P-FILES"
@Prev "P-EGS"
@Toc "Par"

REQTOOLS=YES/NO
===============

This controls the use of @{b}reqtools.library@{ub}. If set to @{b}NO@{ub} then reqtools
will not be used (except in very unusual circumstances). It will still
however be opened and closed. If set to @{b}YES@{ub} then reqtools will be used
for various requesters.

This parameter is not available as a menu option, is not saved in
settings files and can not be specified on a project Icon.

Default values is @{b}YES@{ub}.


@EndNode

@Node "P-FILES" "MPMorph.guide/P-FILES"
@Next "P-HELP"
@Prev "P-REQTOOLS"
@Toc "Par"

FILES=filename
==============

This is only relevant to the @{b}Shell@{ub}, only one name can be supplied -
default is to open a new unnamed project.


@EndNode

@Node "P-HELP" "MPMorph.guide/P-HELP"
@Next "P-KEEPSETTINGS"
@Prev "P-FILES"
@Toc "Par"

HELP=YES/NO
===========

Sets the default value of the @{b}Continuous Help?@{ub} settings menu item -
defaults to @{b}NO@{ub}.

When set to @{b}YES@{ub} help is continuously displayed using amigaguide.


@EndNode

@Node "P-KEEPSETTINGS" "MPMorph.guide/P-KEEPSETTINGS"
@Next "P-SETTINGS"
@Prev "P-HELP"
@Toc "Par"

KEEPSETTINGS=YES/NO
===================

Sets the default value of the @{b}Keep Settings?@{ub} settings menu item -
defaults to @{b}YES@{ub}.

By default current settings are saved in @{b}ENV:MPMorph/MPMorph.prefs@{ub} when
@{b}MPMorph@{ub} is @{b}quit@{ub}. This parameter and menu item enable this behaviour to
be turned off.


@EndNode

@Node "P-SETTINGS" "MPMorph.guide/P-SETTINGS"
@Next "P-ZOOM"
@Prev "P-KEEPSETTINGS"
@Toc "Par"

SETTINGS=filename
=================

This can only be supplied on the @{b}Shell@{ub} command line, or an Icon @{b}Tool
Type@{ub}. It specifies the name of a file for more parameters. See
@{"parameters" Link "Par"}.

This parameter is not changed by Requester loaded projects.


@EndNode

@Node "P-ZOOM" "MPMorph.guide/P-ZOOM"
@Next "P-PREVIEW"
@Prev "P-SETTINGS"
@Toc "Par"

ZOOM=YES/NO/OFF
===============

Sets the default value of the @{b}Zoom?@{ub} settings menu item. If set to @{b}YES@{ub}
then images will be initially displayed 2x normal size, if set to @{b}NO@{ub}
then images will be initially displayed normal size, setting to @{b}OFF@{ub}
disables the @{b}Zoom?@{ub} option, this reduces chip memory usage to 1/5 -
defaults to @{b}NO@{ub}.


@EndNode

@Node "P-PREVIEW" "MPMorph.guide/P-PREVIEW"
@Next "P-USER2"
@Prev "P-ZOOM"
@Toc "Par"

PREVIEW=scriptname
==================

This specifies the name of an ARexx script to run to preview the
rendered image.

The default script is:

@{"Rexx/Preview.MPM" link "Rexx/Preview.MPM/main"}.

See @{"Preview.guide" link "Preview.guide/main"}.

The version supplied displays a GUI to render the image as a 16 colour
grey scale.

It can be changed using the menu item, a requester is displayed
allowing the input of the value.

F1 is a short cut to this script.


@EndNode

@Node "P-USER2" "MPMorph.guide/P-USER2"
@Next "P-USER3"
@Prev "P-PREVIEW"
@Toc "Par"

USER2=scriptname
================

This specifies the name of an ARexx script to run when F2 is pressed.

The default script is:

@{"Rexx/EdgePoints.MPM" link "Rexx/EdgePoints.MPM/main"}.

See @{"EdgePoints.guide" link "EdgePoints.guide/main"}.

This displays a requester to Edge Detect the images.


@EndNode

@Node "P-USER3" "MPMorph.guide/P-USER3"
@Next "P-USER4"
@Prev "P-USER2"
@Toc "Par"

USER3=scriptname
================

This specifies the name of an ARexx script to run when F3 is pressed.

The default script is:

@{"Rexx/IndexHelp.MPM" link "Rexx/IndexHelp.MPM/main"}.

See @{"RunMPIndex.guide" link "RunMPIndex.guide/main"}.

This displays the index of all the help files.


@EndNode

@Node "P-USER4" "MPMorph.guide/P-USER4"
@Next "P-USER5"
@Prev "P-USER3"
@Toc "Par"

USER4=scriptname
================

This specifies the name of an ARexx script to run when F4 is pressed.

The default script is:

@{"Rexx/RTPreview.MPM" link "Rexx/RTPreview.MPM/main"}.

This continuously displays a preview, updating the display when any
editing is done.

Rerun this script to stop the preview rendering.

For fastest previewing set the 24 bit images to grayscale PBM versions
of the rendering size of the images and set the number of frames to 1.


@EndNode

@Node "P-USER5" "MPMorph.guide/P-USER5"
@Next "P-USER6"
@Prev "P-USER4"
@Toc "Par"

USER5=scriptname
================

This specifies the name of an ARexx script to run when F5 is pressed.

There is no default script.


@EndNode

@Node "P-USER6" "MPMorph.guide/P-USER6"
@Next "P-USER7"
@Prev "P-USER5"
@Toc "Par"

USER6=scriptname
================

This specifies the name of an ARexx script to run when F6 is pressed.

There is no default script.


@EndNode

