The Information Window
**********************

This window is always displayed when @{b}MPMorph@{ub} is running. It displays
information about the current project. The window title is @{b}MPMorph@{ub}, the
screen title will be displayed as the project name if the project has a
name. It is used to set up all the information required by @{b}MPRender@{ub}.


 @{" Gadgets  " Link "I-gad"}      Gadgets displayed in the Info Window
 @{" Menus    " Link "I-men"}      Menus available in the Info Window
 @{" Keyboard " Link "I-Key"}      Keyboard controls in the Info Window


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad" "MPMorph.guide/I-gad"
@Next "I-men"
@Toc "Info"

Gadgets in Info Window
======================

@font topaz.font 8

The Information Window appears with gadgets:

     ----------------------------
     |@{"." Link "I-gad-Close"}|@{"MPMorph           " Link "I-gad-Drag"}|@{" " Link "I-gad-Zoom"}|@{" " Link "I-gad-Depth"}|
     |--------------------------|
     |@{"        Help Text         " Link "I-gad-Help"}|
     | File @{u}O@{uu}ne @{"............." Link "I-gad-File_One"} @{"X" Link "I-gad-Get_File_One"}|
     | File @{u}T@{uu}wo @{"............." Link "I-gad-File_One"} @{"X" Link "I-gad-Get_File_Two"}|
     |24 File @{u}1@{uu} @{"............." Link "I-gad-24_File_1"} @{"X" Link "I-gad-Get_24_File_1"}|
     |24 File @{u}2@{uu} @{"............." Link "I-gad-24_File_2"} @{"X" Link "I-gad-Get_24_File_2"}|
     |    Width @{"..." Link "I-gad-Width"}  Height @{"..." Link "I-gad-Height"}|
     |@{" Set Size... " Link "I-gad-SetSize"} @{"  Scale... " Link "I-gad-Scale"}|
     | @{"Single" Link "I-gad-Single"} @{u}F@{uu}rames@{".." Link "I-gad-Frames"} St@{u}a@{uu}rt @{".." Link "I-gad-Start"}|
     |     @{u}N@{uu}ame @{"............" Link "I-gad-Name"}  @{"X" Link "I-gad-Get_Name"}|
     |@{"      Edit Points...      " Link "I-gad-Edit_Points"}|
     ----------------------------


 @{" Help Text      " Link "I-gad-Help"}                    Displays help messages
 @{" File One       " Link "I-gad-File_One"}                    The first image file for point editing
 @{" Get file       " Link "I-gad-Get_File_One"}                    Get file gadget for above
 @{" File Two       " Link "I-gad-File_Two"}                    The second image file for point editing
 @{" Get File       " Link "I-gad-Get_File_Two"}                    Get file gadget for above
 @{" 24 File 1      " Link "I-gad-24_File_1"}                    The first 24 bit image file to morph
 @{" Get File       " Link "I-gad-Get_24_File_1"}                    Get file gadget for above
 @{" 24 File 2      " Link "I-gad-24_File_2"}                    The second 24 bit image file to morph
 @{" Get File       " Link "I-gad-Get_24_File_2"}                    Get file gadget for above
 @{" Width          " Link "I-gad-Width"}                    Read only gadget showing width
 @{" Height         " Link "I-gad-Height"}                    Read only gadget showing Height
 @{" Set Size       " Link "I-gad-SetSize"}                    Set the render size
 @{" Scale          " Link "I-gad-Scale"}                    Scale the render size
 @{" Single         " Link "I-gad-Single"}                    Cycle morph mode gadget
 @{" Frames         " Link "I-gad-Frames"}                    Number of frames to generate
 @{" Start          " Link "I-gad-Start"}                    Frame number to start at
 @{" Name           " Link "I-gad-Name"}                    File name of animation frames
 @{" Get File       " Link "I-gad-Get_Name"}                    Get file gadget for above
 @{" Edit Points... " Link "I-gad-Edit_Points"}                    Display images to edit points

 @{" Close gadget   " Link "I-gad-Close"}                    Quit program
 @{" Drag gadget    " Link "I-gad-Drag"}                    Moe the window
 @{" Zoom gadget    " Link "I-gad-Zoom"}                    Standard zoom window
 @{" Depth gadget   " Link "I-gad-Depth"}                    Standard depth gadget


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad-Help" "MPMorph.guide/I-gad-Help"
@Next "I-gad-File_One"
@Toc "I-gad"

Help Text gadget
----------------

This gadget displays short help messages.

See also @{"Continuous Help" Link "P-HELP"}.


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad-File_One" "MPMorph.guide/I-gad-File_One"
@Next "I-gad-Get_File_One"
@Prev "I-gad-Help"
@Toc "I-gad"

File One gadget
---------------

This gadget allows the editing of the file name of the first image to
be used when editing points. This gadget is disabled if the
@{"Edit Windows" Link "Edit"} are currently open. The file name can be either edited in
the string gadget or by using the @{"Get File" Link "I-gad-Get_File_One"} to display an ASL file
requester.

This image should be a Workbench displayable version of the
@{"first 24 bit file" Link "I-gad-24_File_1"}. It is displayed in the first @{"Edit Window" Link "Edit"} when
editing points.

@{b}o@{ub} can be used to activate this gadget - See @{"Keyboard" Link "I-Key"}.

See @{"File naming" Link "File_Names"} for how to specify the file name.


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad-Get_File_One" "MPMorph.guide/I-gad-Get_File_One"
@Next "I-gad-File_Two"
@Prev "I-gad-File_One"
@Toc "I-gad"

Get File One gadget
-------------------

This gadget displays an ASL file requester to select the file to appear
in the @{"File One" Link "I-gad-File_One"} gadget.

@{b}o@{ub} with @{b}shift@{ub} is the same as using this gadget - See @{"Keyboard" Link "I-Key"}.


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad-File_Two" "MPMorph.guide/I-gad-File_Two"
@Next "I-gad-Get_File_Two"
@Prev "I-gad-Get_File_One"
@Toc "I-gad"

File Two gadget
---------------

This gadget is the same as the @{"File One" Link "I-gad-File_One"} gadget for the second
displayable image. This image should be the same size as the first.

@{b}t@{ub} can be used to activate this gadget - See @{"Keyboard" Link "I-Key"}.

See @{"File naming" Link "File_Names"} for how to specify the file name.


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad-Get_File_Two" "MPMorph.guide/I-gad-Get_File_Two"
@Next "I-gad-24_File_1"
@Prev "I-gad-File_Two"
@Toc "I-gad"

Get File Two gadget
-------------------

This gadget displays an ASL file requester to select the file to appear
in the @{"File Two" Link "I-gad-File_Two"} gadget.

@{b}t@{ub} with @{b}shift@{ub} is the same as using this gadget - See @{"Keyboard" Link "I-Key"}.


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad-24_File_1" "MPMorph.guide/I-gad-24_File_1"
@Next "I-gad-Get_24_File_1"
@Prev "I-gad-Get_File_Two"
@Toc "I-gad"

24 File 1 gadget
----------------

This gadget allows the editing of the file name of the first image to
be used when morphing. The file name can be either edited in the string
gadget or by using the @{"Get File" Link "I-gad-Get_24_File_1"} to display an ASL file requester.

This image should be a 24 bit version of the @{"first displayable file" Link "I-gad-File_One"}.
Note: @{b}MPMorph@{ub} now has the ability to load a large variety of images as
24 bit files. If this gadget is left blank then the name from the
@{"first displayable file" Link "I-gad-File_One"} is used.

@{b}1@{ub} can be used to activate this gadget - See @{"Keyboard" Link "I-Key"}.

See @{"File naming" Link "File_Names"} for how to specify the file name.


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad-Get_24_File_1" "MPMorph.guide/I-gad-Get_24_File_1"
@Next "I-gad-24_File_2"
@Prev "I-gad-24_File_1"
@Toc "I-gad"

Get 24 File 1 gadget
--------------------

This gadget displays an ASL file requester to select the file to appear
in the @{"24 File 1" Link "I-gad-24_File_1"} gadget.

@{b}1@{ub} with @{b}shift@{ub} is the same as using this gadget - See @{"Keyboard" Link "I-Key"}.


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad-24_File_2" "MPMorph.guide/I-gad-24_File_2"
@Next "I-gad-Get_24_File_2"
@Prev "I-gad-Get_24_File_1"
@Toc "I-gad"

24 File 2 gadget
----------------

This gadget allows the editing of the file name of the last image to be
used when morphing. The file name can be either edited in the string
gadget or by using the @{"Get File" Link "I-gad-Get_24_File_2"} to display an ASL file requester.

This image should be a 24 bit version of the @{"second displayable file" Link "I-gad-File_Two"}.
Note: @{b}MPMorph@{ub} now has the ability to load a large variety of images as
24 bit files. If this gadget is left blank then the name from the
@{"second displayable file" Link "I-gad-File_Two"} is used.

If @{"Single Image" Link "I-gad-Single"} mode is selected then this is ignored.

@{b}2@{ub} can be used to activate this gadget - See @{"Keyboard" Link "I-Key"}.

See @{"File naming" Link "File_Names"} for how to specify the file name.


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad-Get_24_File_2" "MPMorph.guide/I-gad-Get_24_File_2"
@Next "I-gad-Width"
@Prev "I-gad-24_File_2"
@Toc "I-gad"

Get 24 File 2 gadget
--------------------

This gadget displays an ASL file requester to select the file to appear
in the @{"24 File 2" Link "I-gad-24_File_2"} gadget.

@{b}2@{ub} with @{b}shift@{ub} is the same as using this gadget - See @{"Keyboard" Link "I-Key"}.


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad-Width" "MPMorph.guide/I-gad-Width"
@Next "I-gad-Height"
@Prev "I-gad-Get_24_File_2"
@Toc "I-gad"

Width gadget
------------

This gadget displays the width of the images being edited. If images
have not been selected then it should display the maximum width of the
current points.


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad-Height" "MPMorph.guide/I-gad-Height"
@Next "I-gad-SetSize"
@Prev "I-gad-Width"
@Toc "I-gad"

Height gadget
-------------

This gadget displays the height of the images being edited. If images
have not been selected then it should display the maximum height of the
current points.


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad-SetSize" "MPMorph.guide/I-gad-SetSize"
@Next "I-gad-Scale"
@Prev "I-gad-Height"
@Toc "I-gad"

Set Size gadget
---------------

This displays a requester, see @{"SetSize" Link "Req-SetSize"}, to set the size of the rendered
image. Points are not scaled.

@{b}z@{ub} is the same as using this gadget - See @{"Keyboard" Link "I-Key"}.


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad-Scale" "MPMorph.guide/I-gad-Scale"
@Next "I-gad-Single"
@Prev "I-gad-SetSize"
@Toc "I-gad"

Scale gadget
------------

This displays a requester, see @{"Scale" Link "Req-Scale"}, to scalet the size of the
rendered image. Points are scaled.

@{b}s@{ub} is the same as using this gadget - See @{"Keyboard" Link "I-Key"}.


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad-Single" "MPMorph.guide/I-gad-Single"
@Next "I-gad-Frames"
@Prev "I-gad-Scale"
@Toc "I-gad"

Single image gadget
-------------------

This gadget cycles between @{b}Morphs@{ub}, @{b}Warps@{ub}, @{b}Animated Morphs@{ub} and @{b}Animated
Warps@{ub}.

In @{b}Warp@{ub} mode one image is distorted based on the control points.

In @{b}Morph@{ub} mode one image is distorted/recoloured into a second image
based on control points.

In @{b}animated Warps@{ub} and @{b}Morphs@{ub} the input images can change on each output
frame.

@{b}r@{ub} and @{b}R@{ub} can be used to cycle this gadget forward and backward - See
@{"Keyboard" Link "I-Key"}.


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad-Frames" "MPMorph.guide/I-gad-Frames"
@Next "I-gad-Start"
@Prev "I-gad-Single"
@Toc "I-gad"

Number of Frames gadget
-----------------------

This gadget can be used to specify the number of frames to generate.

In @{"Single" Link "I-gad-Single"} mode the total number of frames will be this number plus the
first image.

In dual mode the total number of frames is the first image, this number
and the last image.

@{b}f@{ub} can be used to activate this gadget - See @{"Keyboard" Link "I-Key"}.

This gadget is disabled if Images are displayed and an @{b}animated
Morph/Warp@{ub} is being edited.


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad-Start" "MPMorph.guide/I-gad-Start"
@Next "I-gad-Name"
@Prev "I-gad-Frames"
@Toc "I-gad"

Start Frame gadget
------------------

This gadget can be used to specify the number to use in the @{"Name" Link "I-gad-Name"} of the
first generated file. This number is then incremented by 1 for each
subsequent frame.

@{b}a@{ub} can be used to activate this gadget - See @{"Keyboard" Link "I-Key"}.

This gadget is disabled if Images are displayed and an @{b}animated
Morph/Warp@{ub} is being edited.


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad-Name" "MPMorph.guide/I-gad-Name"
@Next "I-gad-Get_Name"
@Prev "I-gad-Start"
@Toc "I-gad"

Anim file Name gadget
---------------------

This gadget is used to name the files produced by @{b}MPRender@{ub}.

The file name can be either edited in the string gadget or by using the
@{"Get File" Link "I-gad-Get_Name"} to display an ASL file requester.

The file name should contain the characters @{b}%ld@{ub}. These characters will
be replaced by the frame number, starting from that specified in the
@{"Start" Link "I-gad-Start"} gadget.

@{b}n@{ub} can be used to activate this gadget - See @{"Keyboard" Link "I-Key"}.

See @{"File naming" Link "File_Names"} for further information on how to specify the file name.


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad-Get_Name" "MPMorph.guide/I-gad-Get_Name"
@Next "I-gad-Edit_Points"
@Prev "I-gad-Name"
@Toc "I-gad"

Get Anim file Name gadget
-------------------------

This gadget displays an ASL file requester to select the file to appear
in the @{"Name" Link "I-gad-Name"} gadget.

@{b}n@{ub} with @{b}shift@{ub} is the same as using this gadget - See @{"Keyboard" Link "I-Key"}.


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad-Edit_Points" "MPMorph.guide/I-gad-Edit_Points"
@Next "I-gad-Close"
@Prev "I-gad-Get_Name"
@Toc "I-gad"

Edit Points... gadget
---------------------

This button gadget has the same effect as the @{"Edit Points" Link "I-men-P-Edit_Points"} menu option.
It opens the @{"Control Window" Link "Con"} and @{"Edit Windows" Link "Edit"} to allow editing of the
control points. If these windows are already open then the Control
Window is activated.

@{b}p@{ub} is the same as using this gadget - See @{"Keyboard" Link "I-Key"}.


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad-Close" "MPMorph.guide/I-gad-Close"
@Next "I-gad-Drag"
@Prev "I-gad-Edit_Points"
@Toc "I-gad"

Close gadget
------------

This is a standard close gadget. Clicking quits the program.

If the current project has been changed but not saved then the
@{"Unsaved Project requester" Link "Req-Unsaved"} is displayed.


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad-Drag" "MPMorph.guide/I-gad-Drag"
@Next "I-gad-Zoom"
@Prev "I-gad-Close"
@Toc "I-gad"

Drag gadget
-----------

This allows the window to be moved.


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad-Zoom" "MPMorph.guide/I-gad-Zoom"
@Next "I-gad-Depth"
@Prev "I-gad-Drag"
@Toc "I-gad"

Zoom gadget
-----------

This is a standard Zoom gadget which switches the window between full
size and a title bar and the help text.


@EndNode

@Node "I-gad-Depth" "MPMorph.guide/I-gad-Depth"
@Prev "I-gad-Zoom"
@Toc "I-gad"

Depth gadget
------------

This is a standard depth gadget.


@EndNode

@Node "I-men" "MPMorph.guide/I-men"
@Next "I-Key"
@Prev "I-gad"
@Toc "Info"

Menus on the Info Window
========================

The following menus are available on the Information Window:


 @{" Project  " Link "I-men-P"}             Project menu

 @{" Settings " Link "men-Settings"}             Settings menu

 @{" User     " Link "I-men-U"}             User menu


@EndNode

@Node "I-men-P" "MPMorph.guide/I-men-P"
@Next "men-Settings"
@Toc "I-men"

Info Window Project menu
------------------------

This menu contains the following items with their associated Amiga
short-cuts in the Info Window:


 @{" New         N " Link "I-men-P-New"}                    Create a new project
 @{" Open...     O " Link "I-men-P-Open"}                    Open a file
 @{" Open Recent   " Link "I-men-P-Recent"}                    Open a Recent file

 @{" Save        S " Link "I-men-P-Save"}                    Save file
 @{" Save As...    " Link "I-men-P-Save_As"}                    Save named file
 @{" Delete...     " Link "I-men-P-Delete"}                    Delete a Project

 @{" About...      " Link "I-men-P-About"}                    Show about requester

 @{" Edit Points E " Link "I-men-P-Edit_Points"}                    Open windows to edit points

 @{" Quit        Q " Link "I-men-P-Quit"}                    Quit program


@EndNode

@Node "I-men-P-New" "MPMorph.guide/I-men-P-New"
@Next "I-men-P-Open"
@Toc "I-men-P"

Info Window Project/New menu item
.................................

This menu item creates a new project.

If the current project has been changed but not saved then the
@{"Unsaved Project requester" Link "Req-Unsaved"} is displayed.


@EndNode

@Node "I-men-P-Open" "MPMorph.guide/I-men-P-Open"
@Next "I-men-P-Recent"
@Prev "I-men-P-New"
@Toc "I-men-P"

Info Window Project/Open menu item
..................................

This menu item allows the loading of a previously created
@{"Parameter file" Link "File_Format"}.

If the current project has been changed but not saved then the
@{"Unsaved Project requester" Link "Req-Unsaved"} is displayed.


@EndNode

@Node "I-men-P-Recent" "MPMorph.guide/I-men-P-Recent"
@Next "I-men-P-Save"
@Prev "I-men-P-Open"
@Toc "I-men-P"

Info Window Project/Recent sub menu
...................................

This list the 5 most recent open files, allowing them to be opened
without a file requester.


 @{" Recent_1  1 " Link "I-men-P-Recent1"}                Most recent file
 @{" Recent_2  2 " Link "I-men-P-Recent2"}                Second most recent file
 @{" Recent_3  3 " Link "I-men-P-Recent3"}                Third most recent file
 @{" Recent_4  4 " Link "I-men-P-Recent4"}                Fourth most recent file
 @{" Recent_5  5 " Link "I-men-P-Recent5"}                Fifth most recent file


@EndNode

@Node "I-men-P-Recent1" "MPMorph.guide/I-men-P-Recent1"
@Toc "I-men-P-Recent"

Info Window Project/Recent 1 menu item
======================================

This opens the most recently opened file.


@EndNode

@Node "I-men-P-Recent2" "MPMorph.guide/I-men-P-Recent2"
@Toc "I-men-P-Recent"

Info Window Project/Recent 2 menu item
======================================

This opens the second most recently opened file.


@EndNode

@Node "I-men-P-Recent3" "MPMorph.guide/I-men-P-Recent3"
@Toc "I-men-P-Recent"

Info Window Project/Recent 3 menu item
======================================

This opens the third most recently opened file.


@EndNode

@Node "I-men-P-Recent4" "MPMorph.guide/I-men-P-Recent4"
@Toc "I-men-P-Recent"

Info Window Project/Recent 4 menu item
======================================

This opens the fourth most recently opened file.


@EndNode

@Node "I-men-P-Recent5" "MPMorph.guide/I-men-P-Recent5"
@Toc "I-men-P-Recent"

Info Window Project/Recent 5 menu item
======================================

This opens the fifth most recently opened file.


@EndNode

@Node "I-men-P-Save" "MPMorph.guide/I-men-P-Save"
@Next "I-men-P-Save_As"
@Prev "I-men-P-Recent"
@Toc "I-men-P"

Info Window Project/Save menu item
..................................

This saves the current project using the current name. If the project
does not yet have a name then an ASL file requester is displayed.

See @{"File Format" Link "File_Format"}.


@EndNode

@Node "I-men-P-Save_As" "MPMorph.guide/I-men-P-Save_As"
@Next "I-men-P-Delete"
@Prev "I-men-P-Save"
@Toc "I-men-P"

Info Window Project/Save As... menu item
........................................

This saves the current project using a name chosen suing an ASL file
requester.

See @{"File Format" Link "File_Format"}.


@EndNode

@Node "I-men-P-Delete" "MPMorph.guide/I-men-P-Delete"
@Next "I-men-P-About"
@Prev "I-men-P-Save_As"
@Toc "I-men-P"

Info Window Project/Delete... menu item
.......................................

This can be used to delete a Project. It will delete the main file, its
icon (if present) and any associated Anim points files.

See @{"File Format" Link "File_Format"}.


@EndNode

@Node "I-men-P-About" "MPMorph.guide/I-men-P-About"
@Next "I-men-P-Edit_Points"
@Prev "I-men-P-Delete"
@Toc "I-men-P"

Info Window Project/About... menu item
......................................

This displays some program version information in the @{"About Requester" Link "Req-About"}.


@EndNode

@Node "I-men-P-Edit_Points" "MPMorph.guide/I-men-P-Edit_Points"
@Next "I-men-P-Quit"
@Prev "I-men-P-About"
@Toc "I-men-P"

Info Window Project/Edit Points menu item
.........................................

This is the same as the @{"Edit Points" Link "I-gad-Edit_Points"} gadget.

It opens the @{"Control Window" Link "Con"} and @{"Edit Windows" Link "Edit"} to allow editing of the
control points. If these windows are already open then the Control
Window is activated.


@EndNode

@Node "I-men-P-Quit" "MPMorph.guide/I-men-P-Quit"
@Prev "I-men-P-Edit_Points"
@Toc "I-men-P"

Info Window Project/Quit menu item
..................................

This quits @{b}MPMorph@{ub}.

If the current project has been changed but not saved then the
@{"Unsaved Project requester" Link "Req-Unsaved"} is displayed.


@EndNode

@Node "men-Settings" "MPMorph.guide/men-Settings"
@Next "I-men-U"
@Prev "I-men-P"
@Toc "I-men"

Settings menu
-------------

This menu contains the following items with their associated Amiga
short-cuts in the @{"Control" Link "Con"}, @{"Info" Link "Info"} and @{"Edit" Link "Edit"} Windows. Settings can be set
using @{"Parameters" Link "Par"}.


 @{" Create Icons?        " Link "P-CREATEICONS"}                Create Icons on projects?
 @{" Zoom?              Z " Link "P-ZOOM"}                Zoom Image?
 @{" Public Screen...     " Link "P-PUBSCREEN"}                Screen for @{b}MPMorph@{ub}
 @{" Custom Mode...       " Link "P-CUSTOMMODE"}                Mode of Custom screen to open
 @{" Custom Depth...      " Link "P-CUSTOMDEPTH"}                Depth of Custom screen to open
 @{" Preview Script...    " Link "P-PREVIEW"}                ARexx preview script

 @{" Create Prefs Icons?  " Link "P-CREATEICONSP"}                Create Icons on settings
 @{" Keep Settings?       " Link "P-KEEPSETTINGS"}                Keep settings on Quit
 @{" Load Settings...     " Link "men-S-LoadS"}                Display file requester to load settings
 @{" Save Settings        " Link "men-S-SaveS"}                Save settings in ENVARC:MPMorph/MPMorph.prefs
 @{" Save Settings As...  " Link "men-S-SaveSAs"}                Display file requester to save settings

 @{" Reset To Defaults    " Link "men-S-ResetD"}                Reset to default settings
 @{" Last Saved           " Link "men-S-LastS"}                Restore from ENVARC:MPMorph/MPMorph.prefs
 @{" Restore              " Link "men-S-Restore"}                Restore from ENV:MPMorph/MPMorph.prefs

 @{" Continuous Help?     " Link "P-HELP"}                Display continuous help


@EndNode

@Node "men-S-LoadS" "MPMorph.guide/men-S-LoadS"
@Next "men-S-SaveS"
@Toc "men-Settings"

Setting/Load Settings... menu item
..................................

This displays an ASL requester to load @{"settings" Link "Par"} into the currently
running program.

The default name is @{b}MPMorph.prefs@{ub}.


@EndNode

@Node "men-S-SaveS" "MPMorph.guide/men-S-SaveS"
@Next "men-S-SaveSAs"
@Prev "men-S-LoadS"
@Toc "men-Settings"

Settings/Save Settings menu item
................................

This saves the current @{"settings" Link "Par"} in @{b}ENVARC:MPMorph/MPMorph.prefs@{ub} and
@{b}ENV:MPMorph/MPMorph.prefs@{ub}.

If @{"CREATEICONSP" Link "P-CREATEICONSP"} is set then an Icon is saved as well

Unless @{"KEEPSETTINGS" Link "P-KEEPSETTINGS"} is set to NO current settings are saved in
@{b}ENV:MPMorph/MPMorph.prefs@{ub} whenever @{b}MPMorph@{ub} is quit.


@EndNode

@Node "men-S-SaveSAs" "MPMorph.guide/men-S-SaveSAs"
@Next "men-S-ResetD"
@Prev "men-S-SaveS"
@Toc "men-Settings"

Setting/Save Settings As... menu item
.....................................

This displays an ASL requester to save the current @{"settings" Link "Par"}.

If @{"CREATEICONSP" Link "P-CREATEICONSP"} is set then an Icon is saved as well

The default name is @{b}MPMorph.prefs@{ub}.


@EndNode

@Node "men-S-ResetD" "MPMorph.guide/men-S-ResetD"
@Next "men-S-LastS"
@Prev "men-S-SaveSAs"
@Toc "men-Settings"

Setting/Reset To Defaults menu item
...................................

This resets @{"settings" Link "Par"} to there default values.

If some @{"Image windows" Link "Edit"} are open and @{"ZOOM" Link "P-ZOOM"} is set to @{b}OFF@{ub} then it will stay
@{b}OFF@{ub}.


@EndNode

@Node "men-S-LastS" "MPMorph.guide/men-S-LastS"
@Next "men-S-Restore"
@Prev "men-S-ResetD"
@Toc "men-Settings"

Settings/Last Saved menu item
.............................

This reset @{"settings" Link "Par"} to the values last saved in
@{b}ENVARC:MPMorph/MPMorph.prefs@{ub} (overridden by any @{b}Tool Types@{ub}).

If some @{"Image windows" Link "Edit"} are open and @{"ZOOM" Link "P-ZOOM"} is set to @{b}OFF@{ub} then it will stay
@{b}OFF@{ub}.


@EndNode

@Node "men-S-Restore" "MPMorph.guide/men-S-Restore"
@Prev "men-S-LastS"
@Toc "men-Settings"

Setting/Restore menu item
.........................

This resets @{"settings" Link "Par"} to the values last saved in
@{b}ENV:MPMorph/MPMorph.prefs@{ub} (overridden by any @{b}Tool Types@{ub}). Settings are
saved in this file whenever @{b}MPMorph@{ub} is quit if @{"KEEPSETTINGS" Link "P-KEEPSETTINGS"} is set to
@{b}YES@{ub}.

If some @{"Image windows" Link "Edit"} are open and @{"ZOOM" Link "P-ZOOM"} is set to @{b}OFF@{ub} then it will stay
@{b}OFF@{ub}.


@EndNode

