@Node "I-Key" "MPMorph.guide/I-Key"
@Prev "I-men"
@Toc "Info"

Keyboard controls in the Info Window
====================================

The following keyboard controls are available in the Info Window:

     @{b}o@{ub}  Activate @{"File One" Link "I-gad-File_One"} gadget
        With @{b}shift@{ub} - show file requester - See @{"Get File One" Link "I-gad-Get_File_One"}.
     
     @{b}t@{ub}  Activate @{"File Two" Link "I-gad-File_Two"} gadget
        With @{b}shift@{ub} - show file requester - See @{"Get File Two" Link "I-gad-Get_File_Two"}.
     
     @{b}1@{ub}  Activate @{"24 File 1" Link "I-gad-24_File_1"} gadget
        With @{b}shift@{ub} - show file requester - See @{"Get 24 File 1" Link "I-gad-Get_24_File_1"}.
     
     @{b}2@{ub}  Activate @{"24 File 2" Link "I-gad-24_File_2"} gadget
        With @{b}shift@{ub} - show file requester - See @{"Get 24 File 2" Link "I-gad-Get_24_File_2"}.
     
     @{b}zZ@{ub} Same as @{"Set Size" Link "I-gad-SetSize"} gadget.
     
     @{b}sS@{ub} Same as @{"Scale" Link "I-gad-Scale"} gadget.
     
     @{b}rR@{ub} Cycle @{"Single image" Link "I-gad-Single"} gadget.
     
     @{b}f@{ub}  Activate @{"Frames" Link "I-gad-Frames"} gadget.
     
     @{b}a@{ub}  Activate @{"Start" Link "I-gad-Start"} gadget.
     
     @{b}n@{ub}  Activate @{"Name" Link "I-gad-Name"} gadget
        With @{b}shift@{ub} - show file requester - See @{"Get Name" Link "I-gad-Get_Name"}.
     
     @{b}p@{ub}  Same as @{"Edit Points" Link "I-gad-Edit_Points"} gadget

@{b}Help@{ub} displays context sensitive help using @{b}amigaguide@{ub}.


@EndNode

@Node "Con" "MPMorph.guide/Con"
@Next "Edit"
@Prev "Info"
@Toc "Main"

The Control Window
******************

The control window displays various gadgets for different for different
point editing modes. The title bar displays the current editing mode as
does the Mouse pointer. The screen title bar displays @{b}MPMorph@{ub} for
non-animated Warps/Morphs and @{b}MPMorph - Frame nnn@{ub} for animated
Warps/Morphs.


 @{" Gadgets    " Link "Con-gad"}        Gadgets displayed in the control window
 @{" Menus      " Link "CI-men"}        Menus on the Control Window
 @{" Edit Modes " Link "EModes"}        Point editing modes
 @{" Keyboard   " Link "Con-Key"}        Keyboard controls in the Control Window


@EndNode

@Node "Con-gad" "MPMorph.guide/Con-gad"
@Next "CI-men"
@Toc "Con"

Control and Image Window gadgets
================================

@font topaz.font 8

The Control Window appears with gadgets:

     --------------
     |@{"." Link "Con-gad-Close"}|@{" Mov " Link "Con-gad-Drag"}|@{"  " Link "Con-gad-Depth"}|
     |------------|
     |@{" ONE " Link "EMode-One"} @{" TWO " Link "EMode-Two"}|
     |@{" REL " Link "EMode-Relative"} @{" ADD " Link "EMode-Add"}|
     |@{" DEL " Link "EMode-Delete"} @{" LNK " Link "EMode-Link"}|
     |@{" UNL " Link "EMode-Unlink"} @{" MOV " Link "EMode-Move"}|
     |@{"|<" Link "Con-gad-First"}@{"<-" Link "Con-gad-Previous"}@{"?" Link "Con-gad-Goto"}@{"->" Link "Con-gad-Next"}@{">|" Link "Con-gad-Last"}|
     --------------

Most are used to set the edit mode. The rest except the close and depth
gadgets are used to set the current @{"Frame Number" Link "Req-FrameNumber"}.


 @{" One   " Link "EMode-One"}                 Move points in one window
 @{" Two   " Link "EMode-Two"}                 Move points in both windows
 @{" Rel   " Link "EMode-Relative"}                 Move points relatively in both windows
 @{" Add   " Link "EMode-Add"}                 Add a new point
 @{" Del   " Link "EMode-Delete"}                 Delete an existing point
 @{" Lnk   " Link "EMode-Link"}                 Link two points
 @{" Unl   " Link "EMode-Unlink"}                 Unlink two points
 @{" Mov   " Link "EMode-Move"}                 Scroll the window

 @{" |<    " Link "Con-gad-First"}                 First Frame
 @{" <     " Link "Con-gad-Previous"}                 Previous Frame
 @{" ?     " Link "Con-gad-Goto"}                 Goto Frame
 @{" >     " Link "Con-gad-Next"}                 Next Frame
 @{" >|    " Link "Con-gad-Last"}                 Last Frame

 @{" Close " Link "Con-gad-Close"}                 Close window
 @{" Drag  " Link "Con-gad-Drag"}                Close window
 @{" Depth " Link "Con-gad-Depth"}                 Depth gadget


@EndNode

@Node "Con-gad-First" "MPMorph.guide/Con-gad-First"
@Next "Con-gad-Previous"
@Toc "Con-gad"

Control Window First Frame gadget
---------------------------------

This gadget goes to the first frame. This is the same as the @{"First" Link "CI-men-E-Frame-First"} menu
item.

This gadget is disabled if the Morph/Warp is not animated, or the first
frame is already displayed.


@EndNode

@Node "Con-gad-Previous" "MPMorph.guide/Con-gad-Previous"
@Next "Con-gad-Goto"
@Prev "Con-gad-First"
@Toc "Con-gad"

Control Window Previous Frame gadget
------------------------------------

This gadget goes to the previous frame. This is the same as the
@{"Previous" Link "CI-men-E-Frame-Previous"} menu item.

This gadget is disabled if the Morph/Warp is not animated, or the first
frame is currently displayed.


@EndNode

@Node "Con-gad-Goto" "MPMorph.guide/Con-gad-Goto"
@Next "Con-gad-Next"
@Prev "Con-gad-Previous"
@Toc "Con-gad"

Control Window Goto Frame gadget
--------------------------------

This gadget goes to a chosen frame. This is the same as the @{"Goto" Link "CI-men-E-Frame-Goto"} menu
item. It displays the @{"Frame Number" Link "Req-FrameNumber"} Requester.

This gadget is disabled if the Morph/Warp is not animated.


@EndNode

@Node "Con-gad-Next" "MPMorph.guide/Con-gad-Next"
@Next "Con-gad-Last"
@Prev "Con-gad-Goto"
@Toc "Con-gad"

Control Window Next Frame gadget
--------------------------------

This gadget goes to the next frame. This is the same as the @{"Next" Link "CI-men-E-Frame-Next"} menu
item.

This gadget is disabled if the Morph/Warp is not animated, or the last
frame is currently displayed.


@EndNode

@Node "Con-gad-Last" "MPMorph.guide/Con-gad-Last"
@Next "Con-gad-Close"
@Prev "Con-gad-Next"
@Toc "Con-gad"

Control Window Last Frame gadget
--------------------------------

This gadget goes to the last frame. This is the same as the @{"Last" Link "CI-men-E-Frame-Last"} menu
item.

This gadget is disabled if the Morph/Warp is not animated, or the last
frame is already displayed.


@EndNode

@Node "Con-gad-Close" "MPMorph.guide/Con-gad-Close"
@Next "Con-gad-Drag"
@Prev "Con-gad-Last"
@Toc "Con-gad"

Control Window Close gadget
---------------------------

This closes the @{"Control Window" Link "Con"}, and the @{"Edit Windows" Link "Edit"}.


@EndNode

@Node "Con-gad-Drag" "MPMorph.guide/Con-gad-Drag"
@Next "Con-gad-Depth"
@Prev "Con-gad-Close"
@Toc "Con-gad"

Control Window Drag gadget
--------------------------

This is a standard drag gadget.


@EndNode

@Node "Con-gad-Depth" "MPMorph.guide/Con-gad-Depth"
@Prev "Con-gad-Drag"
@Toc "Con-gad"

Control Window Depth gadget
---------------------------

This is a standard depth gadget.


@EndNode

@Node "CI-men" "MPMorph.guide/CI-men"
@Prev "Con-gad"
@Toc "Con"

Control and Edit Windows menus
==============================

The following menus are available on the @{"Control" Link "Con"} and @{"Edit" Link "Edit"} Windows:


 @{" Project  " Link "CI-men-P"}             Project menu

 @{" Edit     " Link "CI-men-E"}             Edit menu

 @{" Settings " Link "men-Settings"}             Settings menu

 @{" User     " Link "I-men-U"}             User menu


@EndNode

@Node "CI-men-P" "MPMorph.guide/CI-men-P"
@Next "CI-men-E"
@Toc "CI-men"

Control and Edit Windows Project menu
-------------------------------------

This menu contains the following items with their associated Amiga
short-cuts in the @{"Control" Link "Con"} and @{"Edit" Link "Edit"} Windows:


 @{" New Points     N " Link "CI-men-P-New"}                     Delete all points
 @{" Open Points... O " Link "CI-men-P-Open"}                     Read points from a file

 @{" Save           S " Link "CI-men-P-Save"}                     Save file
 @{" Save As...     A " Link "CI-men-P-Save_As"}                     Save named file

 @{" About...         " Link "CI-men-P-About"}                     Show about requester

 @{" Exit Points      " Link "CI-men-P-Exit_Points"}                     Open windows to edit points

 @{" Quit           Q " Link "CI-men-P-Quit"}                     Quit program


@EndNode

@Node "CI-men-P-New" "MPMorph.guide/CI-men-P-New"
@Next "CI-men-P-Open"
@Toc "CI-men-P"

Control and Edit Window Project/New Points menu item
....................................................

This menu item deletes all existing points.


@EndNode

@Node "CI-men-P-Open" "MPMorph.guide/CI-men-P-Open"
@Next "CI-men-P-Save"
@Prev "CI-men-P-New"
@Toc "CI-men-P"

Control and Edit Window Project/Open Points menu item
.....................................................

This menu item allows the loading of a previously created
@{"Parameter file" Link "File_Format"}.

Only the points are loaded from the file. Other parameters are retained.

If the current project has been changed but not saved then the
@{"Unsaved Project requester" Link "Req-Unsaved"} is displayed.


@EndNode

@Node "CI-men-P-Save" "MPMorph.guide/CI-men-P-Save"
@Next "CI-men-P-Save_As"
@Prev "CI-men-P-Open"
@Toc "CI-men-P"

Control and Edit Window Project/Save menu item
..............................................

This saves the current project using the current name. If the project
does not yet have a name then an ASL file requester is displayed.

See @{"File Format" Link "File_Format"}.


@EndNode

@Node "CI-men-P-Save_As" "MPMorph.guide/CI-men-P-Save_As"
@Next "CI-men-P-About"
@Prev "CI-men-P-Save"
@Toc "CI-men-P"

Control and Edit Window Project/Save As... menu item
....................................................

This saves the current project using a name chosen using an ASL file
requester.

See @{"File Format" Link "File_Format"}.


@EndNode

@Node "CI-men-P-About" "MPMorph.guide/CI-men-P-About"
@Next "CI-men-P-Exit_Points"
@Prev "CI-men-P-Save_As"
@Toc "CI-men-P"

Control and Edit Window Project/About... menu item
..................................................

This displays some program version information in the @{"About Requester" Link "Req-About"}.


@EndNode

@Node "CI-men-P-Exit_Points" "MPMorph.guide/CI-men-P-Exit_Points"
@Next "CI-men-P-Quit"
@Prev "CI-men-P-About"
@Toc "CI-men-P"

Control and Edit Window Project/Exit Points menu item
.....................................................

This is the same as closing the @{"Control Window" Link "Con-gad-Close"} or either of the
@{"Edit Windows" Link "E-gad-Close"}. It closes all of these windows.


@EndNode

@Node "CI-men-P-Quit" "MPMorph.guide/CI-men-P-Quit"
@Prev "CI-men-P-Exit_Points"
@Toc "CI-men-P"

Control and Edit Window Project/Quit menu item
..............................................

This quits @{b}MPMorph@{ub}.

If the current project has been changed but not saved then the
@{"Unsaved Project requester" Link "Req-Unsaved"} is displayed.


@EndNode

@Node "CI-men-E" "MPMorph.guide/CI-men-E"
@Prev "CI-men-P"
@Toc "CI-men"

Control and Edit Window Edit menu
---------------------------------

This menu contains the following items with their associated Amiga
short-cuts in the @{"Control" Link "Con"} and @{"Edit" Link "Edit"} Windows:


 @{" Add Grid... G " Link "CI-men-E-Grid"}                     Add a grid of points
 @{" Triangulate T " Link "CI-men-E-Triangulate"}                     Convert links to triangles
 @{" Frame       » " Link "CI-men-E-Frame"}                     Change the Frame Number
 @{" Mode        » " Link "CI-men-E-EMode"}                     Set the edit mode.


@EndNode

@Node "CI-men-E-Grid" "MPMorph.guide/CI-men-E-Grid"
@Next "CI-men-E-Triangulate"
@Toc "CI-men-E"

Control and Edit Window Edit/Add Grid... menu item
..................................................

This menu item displays the @{"Add Grid" Link "Req-Add_Grid"} requester to add a grid of points
to the images.


@EndNode

@Node "CI-men-E-Triangulate" "MPMorph.guide/CI-men-E-Triangulate"
@Next "CI-men-E-Frame"
@Prev "CI-men-E-Grid"
@Toc "CI-men-E"

Control and Edit Window Edit/Triangulate menu item
..................................................

This menu item deletes all links between points and attempts to convert
them to triangles. If the current project has been changed then the
@{"Unsaved Project" Link "Req-Unsaved"} requester is displayed.


@EndNode

@Node "CI-men-E-Frame" "MPMorph.guide/CI-men-E-Frame"
@Next "CI-men-E-EMode"
@Prev "CI-men-E-Triangulate"
@Toc "CI-men-E"

Control and Edit Windows Frame sub menu
.......................................

This sub menu contains the following items with their associated Amiga
short-cuts in the @{"Control" Link "Con"} and @{"Edit" Link "Edit"} Windows:


 @{" First    < " Link "CI-men-E-Frame-First"}                        First Frame
 @{" Previous - " Link "CI-men-E-Frame-Previous"}                        Previous Frame
 @{" Goto...  . " Link "CI-men-E-Frame-Goto"}                        Goto Frame
 @{" Next     + " Link "CI-men-E-Frame-Next"}                        Next Frame
 @{" Last     > " Link "CI-men-E-Frame-Last"}                        Last Frame


@EndNode

@Node "CI-men-E-Frame-First" "MPMorph.guide/CI-men-E-Frame-First"
@Toc "CI-men-E-Frame"

Control and Edit Windows Frame/First menu item
**********************************************

This menu item goes to the first frame. This is the same as the @{"First" Link "Con-gad-First"}
gadget.

This menu item is disabled if the Morph/Warp is not animated, or the
first frame is already displayed.


@EndNode

@Node "CI-men-E-Frame-Previous" "MPMorph.guide/CI-men-E-Frame-Previous"
@Toc "CI-men-E-Frame"

Control and Edit Windows Frame/Previous menu item
*************************************************

This menu item goes to the previous frame. This is the same as the
@{"Previous" Link "Con-gad-Previous"} gadget.

This menu item is disabled if the Morph/Warp is not animated, or the
first frame is already displayed.


@EndNode

@Node "CI-men-E-Frame-Goto" "MPMorph.guide/CI-men-E-Frame-Goto"
@Toc "CI-men-E-Frame"

Control and Edit Windows Frame/Goto menu item
*********************************************

This menu item goes to a chosen frame. This is the same as the @{"Goto" Link "Con-gad-Goto"}
gadget. It displays the @{"Frame Number" Link "Req-FrameNumber"} Requester.

This menu item is disabled if the Morph/Warp is not animated, or the
first frame is already displayed.


@EndNode

@Node "CI-men-E-Frame-Next" "MPMorph.guide/CI-men-E-Frame-Next"
@Toc "CI-men-E-Frame"

Control and Edit Windows Frame/Next menu item
*********************************************

This menu item goes to the next frame. This is the same as the @{"Next" Link "Con-gad-Next"}
gadget.

This menu item is disabled if the Morph/Warp is not animated, or the
last frame is already displayed.


@EndNode

@Node "CI-men-E-Frame-Last" "MPMorph.guide/CI-men-E-Frame-Last"
@Toc "CI-men-E-Frame"

Control and Edit Windows Frame/Last menu item
*********************************************

This menu item goes to the last frame. This is the same as the @{"Last" Link "Con-gad-Last"}
gadget.

This menu item is disabled if the Morph/Warp is not animated, or the
last frame is already displayed.


@EndNode

@Node "CI-men-E-EMode" "MPMorph.guide/CI-men-E-EMode"
@Prev "CI-men-E-Frame"
@Toc "CI-men-E"

Control and Edit Window Edit/Mode sub menu
..........................................

This sub menu contains the following items with their associated Amiga
short-cuts in the @{"Control" Link "Con"} and @{"Edit" Link "Edit"} Windows:


 @{" Edit One  1 " Link "EMode-One"}               Move points in one window
 @{" Edit Two  2 " Link "EMode-Two"}               Move points in both windows
 @{" Edit Rel  3 " Link "EMode-Relative"}               Move points relatively in both windows
 @{" Add       4 " Link "EMode-Add"}               Add a new point
 @{" Delete    5 " Link "EMode-Delete"}               Delete an existing point
 @{" Link      6 " Link "EMode-Link"}               Link two points
 @{" Unlink    7 " Link "EMode-Unlink"}               Unlink two points
 @{" None      8 " Link "EMode-Move"}               Scroll the window


